# The Full Story of Remote OK – From 2015 MVP to Multi-Million Dollar Remote Job Board

Remote OK (remoteok.com / originally remoteok.io) is one of the most successful indie-built job boards in the world — focused 100% on **remote jobs**.

It was created single-handedly by Dutch indie hacker / digital nomad **Pieter Levels** (@levelsio), and remains one of his flagship projects along with Nomad List.

## Quick Timeline

- **Late 2014** — Started as "Nomad Jobs" (simple remote-friendly job listings tied to Nomad List community)
- **February 2015** — Re-launched / spun out as standalone **Remote OK** (remoteok.io)
- **February 22, 2015** — Launched on Product Hunt → reached #1 that day with \~1,000 upvotes (became one of the highest voted products ever at the time)
- **2015–2019** → Steady growth among early digital nomads, indie hackers and remote-first startups
- **2020–2021** → Exploded during COVID remote work boom (many sources report \~$30k–$50k/month at peaks)
- **2022–2025** → Became consistent multi-million ARR business (reports of $1.5M–$3.4M+ annual revenue in different years)
- **2026 (current)** → Still #1 most visited remote-only job board, posting tens of thousands of jobs, serving millions of remote workers

## Origin & Motivation (2014–2015)

Pieter Levels was deep into his famous "12 startups in 12 months" challenge (2014).

He had already launched **Nomad List** (mid-2014) — a crowd-sourced database ranking cities for digital nomads (internet speed, cost of living, safety, etc.).

Very quickly he noticed the biggest pain point in the community:

> "Everyone wants to become location-independent… but almost no centralized place existed to find actual **remote jobs**."

Jobs were scattered across AngelList, HN "Who is hiring?", Reddit, separate company career pages — no dedicated remote filter.

So in late 2014 he started aggregating remote-friendly listings under "Nomad Jobs".

In **February 2015** he gave it a clean domain + brand: **Remote OK**.

Key principles from day one (classic Pieter Levels style):

- Minimal MVP (vanilla HTML + jQuery + PHP + SQLite)
- Built + launched in weeks
- Aggregated jobs automatically (scraping + API pulls + manual moderation later)
- Monetized via paid job postings from the beginning (\~$200–$300 per post initially)
- No team, no VC, no office — 100% bootstrapped & remote

## The Product Hunt Launch (Feb 2015)

Pieter submitted Remote OK to Product Hunt on Sunday morning (early SF time).

It shot to #1 that day.

Reached top 15 highest-voted products **of all time** on PH (back when PH was at peak influence).

This gave massive early traction among tech / startup / indie people — exactly the audience that cared about remote work in 2015.

## Growth Phases

**2015–2019** — Niche indie / nomad phase  
Mostly known in digital nomad circles, indie hackers, early remote companies (Buffer, GitLab, Automattic, Basecamp).

**2020–2022** — COVID super-cycle  
Remote work went mainstream → traffic & revenue exploded.  
Multiple reports show peaks of **$40k–$50k+ MRR** (\~$500k–$600k ARR).

**2023–2026** — Mature #1 remote job platform  
- 1M+ remote jobs indexed over lifetime  
- Millions of monthly visitors  
- Revenue consistently reported in **$1.5M–$3.4M ARR** range (sometimes higher)  
- Still solo-maintained (with automation + occasional contractors for support/moderation)  
- Added features: OpenSalaries, async/remote filters, distributed team tags, AI-related job tags, premium subscriptions for job seekers

## Business & Revenue Model

- **Core revenue**: Companies pay to post jobs (one-time or featured)  
- Pricing evolved over time (hundreds to thousands per post depending on promotion)  
- Very high margins (almost no staff, low server costs)  
- No ads on the site itself (clean UX focus)  
- Secondary: job seeker premium access (rarely emphasized)

## Why It Won

- First-mover in pure-remote job niche (2015)  
- Extremely simple, fast, no-BS UX  
- Strong SEO (ranks #1–3 for "remote jobs" variants)  
- Pieter's personal brand & Twitter audience gave free distribution  
- Timing: rode both digital nomad wave (2010s) + full remote mainstream wave (2020s)  
- 100% focus on remote — no hybrid/office dilution

## Current Status (March 2026)

Remote OK remains the #1 most trafficked remote-only job board.

Still owned & operated by Pieter Levels.

Domain: https://remoteok.com

Still minimalist, fast-loading, thousands of live listings daily.

Frequently cited as one of the best examples of **indie hacking success** — built by one person → multi-million dollar business → still running 11 years later.

